<TITLE> Court hears tax-evasion case against Sarwar's brother </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)A Barisal court started hearing witnesses in a tax evasion case against the mayor Mujibur Rahman Sarwar's brother, a ward commissioner and ten others, police said. Plaintiff Shubhash Chandra Roy, divisional engineer of Barisal T&T testified before Barisal Metropolitan Magistrate Munim Hasan's court Wednesday. Another 20 witnesses are to start testifying against the accused Thursday. As per the case details, T&T divisional engineer Shubhash Chandra Roy filed the case on March 13 with the Kotwali police station for realizing about Tk one crore in unpaid telephone bills. The investigating officer submitted charge sheet in this connection on May 03 against ten people including Barisal mayor Sarwar's brother Mizanur Rahman Wahid and commissioner Mosharraf Hossain Badshah. Seven of the accused persons including Mizanur Rahman Wahid and commissioner Badshah are absconding. bdnews2
